8. multos fortis: et is omitted because fortis joins with viros to denote a single conception. â€”praefeetura Reatina: Reate was an ancient town of the Sabines in central Italy. That Cicero selected his men from among the citizens of Reate is explained by the fact that he was the patron of their town and could trust their loyalty. A praefectura was an Italian town or community originally governed by a Roman official (praefectus iuri dicundo). After all Italians had obtained the full Roman citizenship, the term praefectura, as well as the names municipium and colonia, continued to exist only as a historica] reminiscence.
